      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, so you're saying it's \"dangerous\" to rely on renewables alone. but what about the other side? a lot of people say that the risks of nuclear—like the waste and the potential for meltdowns—are way more dangerous than the instability of a renewable grid. isn't it a bit of a stretch to call nuclear an \"essential\" part of the solution when it has those kinds of permanent risks?",
